am Market, also in Suffolk, is associated with a large Roman settlement in nearby Hacheston. The surname is now also common in Ireland (Wexford), where it was taken in the 17th century.","History: Thomas Wickham is recorded as a freeman of Weathersfield, CT, in 1658."]}]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Alice Wykeham was born about 1300 as the daughter of Wykeham. She had at least 5 daughters with John Akemore."},"et":{"about 1300–":"umbes 1300–Surnud","1290–Male":"1290–Surnud","1300–Female":"1300–Surnud","1300–Male":"1300–Surnud","1330–Female":"1330–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1300":"1300","1330":"1330","about 1300":"umbes 1300","about 1330":"umbes 1330","1290":"1290"},"fi":{"about 1300–":"noin 1300–Kuollut","1290–Male":"1290–Kuollut","1300–Female":"1300–Kuollut","1300–Male":"1300–Kuollut","1330–Female":"1330–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1300":"1300","1330":"1330","about 1300":"noin 1300","about 1330":"noin 1330","1290":"1290"},"fr":{"about 1300–":"environ 1300–Décédée","1290–Male":"1290–Décédé","1300–Female":"1300–Décédée","1300–Male":"1300–Décédé","1330–Female":"1330–Décédée","–Male":"Décédé","1300":"1300","1330":"1330","about 1300":"environ 1300"